103
00:05:11,128 --> 00:05:12,389
[SPEAKER_17]: So we'll have to carry on without him.

104
00:05:12,429 --> 00:05:14,470
[SPEAKER_17]: So if you see some shifting around in terms of like

105
00:05:15,043 --> 00:05:20,666
[SPEAKER_17]: you know, who all we're hearing from and who emails are coming from, that's part of what's going on.

106
00:05:20,746 --> 00:05:28,290
[SPEAKER_17]: So we'll see Matt, I think, in at least one more meeting, but then he has informed us that we're not invited.

107
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:34,013
[SPEAKER_17]: So we'll have to just all be sad together while Matt's off getting married and having fun.

108
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:36,194
[SPEAKER_23]: Limited capacity.

109
00:05:38,131 --> 00:05:38,832
[SPEAKER_17]: Thanks, Matt.

110
00:05:40,172 --> 00:06:01,003
[SPEAKER_17]: I think the other thing I wanted to make sure that we provided an update on is right before Memorial Day, the project team, the mayor and myself had a chance to have a meeting with the MSBA, where we were able to talk to them about a number of things, including some of their comments and.

111
00:06:02,215 --> 00:06:04,117
[SPEAKER_17]: It was like a super productive meeting.

112
00:06:04,137 --> 00:06:09,522
[SPEAKER_17]: We were able to talk to them a bit about the deed restriction.

113
00:06:10,623 --> 00:06:24,995
[SPEAKER_17]: We gave them an update on some of the changes that we made to the C-2-2 and the C-3-4 option and let them know what had happened earlier that week in our elimination of the D option that was up on the field.

114
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,392
[SPEAKER_17]: And they were pleased by that.

115
00:06:28,752 --> 00:06:35,916
[SPEAKER_17]: I asked them very directly whether we were in violation of the regulations or in trouble in some way.

116
00:06:35,936 --> 00:06:39,499
[SPEAKER_17]: And they said, no, that we are not.

117
00:06:39,579 --> 00:06:42,380
[SPEAKER_17]: They understand that these things do happen.

118
00:06:43,161 --> 00:06:50,466
[SPEAKER_17]: And what they did ask for was a statement from the city's attorneys sort of weighing in on

119
00:06:51,517 --> 00:07:01,221
[SPEAKER_17]: the changes that were made and the sort of prevailing issues with the deed restriction and how that would work with the project going forward.

120
00:07:01,281 --> 00:07:03,822
[SPEAKER_17]: So all of that work is in motion.

121
00:07:04,482 --> 00:07:18,428
[SPEAKER_17]: They went on to say that it's super common that deed restrictions sort of pop up when you're talking about school building projects because of the way schools were built over time on land that changed hands many, many times.

122
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:31,830
[SPEAKER_17]: So they were satisfied with the disclosures that we had provided, as well as with what we had done to adjust for it, and they were, like, really pleased by that.

123
00:07:32,851 --> 00:07:46,962
[SPEAKER_17]: The other thing that we talked to them a bit about, and I know that I asked them some direct questions about, was their—one of their requests in their comments about our PDP submission was for us to explore a 9-12 only option.

124
00:07:49,047 --> 00:08:06,642
[SPEAKER_17]: I highlighted for them that the reaction here in Medford was sort of a question about whether we had done something wrong or whether the MSBA was telling us that they were going to disapprove of our project going forward if we did not make reductions to

125
00:08:07,363 --> 00:08:09,245
[SPEAKER_17]: only accommodate for a 9 to 12 school.

126
00:08:10,105 --> 00:08:25,718
[SPEAKER_17]: And they unequivocally said that was not the case at all, but that when they saw that we were evaluating a bunch of options that relatively are the same from a square footage perspective, they felt like it was important for us to put some options on the table.

127
00:08:26,878 --> 00:08:31,540
[SPEAKER_17]: for comparison purposes that would explore different square footages.

128
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:34,121
[SPEAKER_17]: And so that's the genesis of their question.

129
00:08:34,801 --> 00:08:42,143
[SPEAKER_17]: They went on to say that they're very supportive of our community building the building that we need it to be.

130
00:08:43,544 --> 00:08:52,307
[SPEAKER_17]: And they just wanted us to sort of explore all of those choices in a variety of ways so that as we go forward,

131
00:08:53,307 --> 00:09:08,155
[SPEAKER_17]: We can all confidently say that we left no stone unturned in the feasibility study to make sure that we were sort of checking out all of the possibilities before us, because this is the time to do that.

132
00:09:08,255 --> 00:09:16,780
[SPEAKER_17]: So I know I felt good about their comments and the communication that we had.

133
00:09:17,518 --> 00:09:24,621
[SPEAKER_17]: Um, we did talk to them a fair bit about our pathway forward through the month of June, um, including a decision on June 10th.

134
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:37,688
[SPEAKER_17]: And, um, overall, um, they were helpful and forthright and collaborative and the good partners that, um, you know, we, we have always expected them to be, and they continue to be.

135
00:09:37,748 --> 00:09:46,412
[SPEAKER_17]: So I just wanted to share that update in case it's helpful for anybody, um, and to make sure that, um, we are continuing to,

136
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:52,901
[SPEAKER_17]: um, address, um, some of the community's concerns, particularly around the deep restriction.

137
00:09:52,961 --> 00:09:53,181
[SPEAKER_17]: So.

138
00:09:54,121 --> 00:10:13,127
[SPEAKER_17]: Um, all signs are ago for the options that we're moving forward with, and I'm excited, um, for our community forum later this week, where we'll get to, um, hear from our community about the things that matter to them in this project and the, um, uh, help us make that choice.

139
00:10:13,207 --> 00:10:13,847
[SPEAKER_17]: So we're.

140
00:10:14,554 --> 00:10:17,175
[SPEAKER_17]: We're down to four or five options and we need to get to one.

141
00:10:18,596 --> 00:10:21,237
[SPEAKER_17]: And I'm excited to hear what folks have to say about that.

142
00:10:22,777 --> 00:10:25,238
[SPEAKER_17]: So those are the updates I wanted to share.

143
00:10:25,778 --> 00:10:40,524
[SPEAKER_17]: The other thing I will mention for the entire group is that we have begun working on scheduling for our next phase of the project, which is really gonna take us from July through February of next year through schematic design.

144
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:55,417
[SPEAKER_17]: And in the coming weeks, we'll finalize that schedule and we'll be sort of trying to check as many calendars as we can to make sure that we're not tripping on other community meetings.

145
00:10:55,457 --> 00:11:01,721
[SPEAKER_17]: I know that's always a huge concern and that we're making decisions when people can tune in and be part of it.

146
00:11:01,821 --> 00:11:09,945
[SPEAKER_17]: So all of that to come and to say to look out for an updated meeting schedule in the next couple of weeks.

147
00:11:11,325 --> 00:11:15,267
[SPEAKER_17]: Um, with that said, we'll get onto the main event.

148
00:11:15,787 --> 00:11:21,450
[SPEAKER_17]: Um, and we have two things, um, happening, uh, two big things happening tonight.

149
00:11:21,530 --> 00:11:30,515
[SPEAKER_17]: The next item on the agenda is an update from the city of Medford on its capital projects and the preliminary, um, thoughts around cost impact.

150
00:11:30,635 --> 00:11:40,220
[SPEAKER_17]: So just like we have been saying all along in terms of our cost estimates, right, this is a kind of a funnel of information that's going to continue to be refined.

151
00:11:40,772 --> 00:11:48,016
[SPEAKER_17]: really all the way through February on the cost side when we have our final schematic design and the estimates.

152
00:11:48,736 --> 00:11:52,939
[SPEAKER_17]: So everything that we've been doing so far is based on lots of broad assumptions.

153
00:11:54,032 --> 00:11:59,077
[SPEAKER_17]: And many, many unknowns, substantial contingencies and all of those good things.

154
00:11:59,657 --> 00:12:03,941
[SPEAKER_17]: The same kind of process has to happen on the, how will we pay for this side of the house?

155
00:12:05,463 --> 00:12:16,653
[SPEAKER_17]: So tonight, I think we'll see from the city team, some of their first steps in framing sort of the work ahead on the city side.

156
00:12:17,513 --> 00:12:31,701
[SPEAKER_17]: And just a quick note that this is sort of, again, the beginning, not the end of the conversation, which will continue with the project team later this week as we keep talking about how do we refine these assumptions?

157
00:12:31,781 --> 00:12:33,902
[SPEAKER_17]: How do we fund this project?

158
00:12:33,942 --> 00:12:34,522
[SPEAKER_17]: Where do we look?

159
00:12:35,663 --> 00:12:36,523
[SPEAKER_17]: And all of that good stuff.

160
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:38,404
[SPEAKER_17]: So we are at the beginning.

161
00:12:38,444 --> 00:12:38,944
[SPEAKER_17]: So here we go.

162
00:12:38,964 --> 00:12:40,986
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm going to turn it over to Mayor Longo Kern.

163
00:12:43,667 --> 00:12:45,648
[SPEAKER_30]: Thank you, Member Graham.

164
00:12:48,028 --> 00:12:51,090
[SPEAKER_30]: I'm going to just introduce city staff that are on the call.

165
00:12:51,951 --> 00:12:56,494
[SPEAKER_30]: And I'm sorry, on my phone, because my camera wasn't working for my computer at home.

166
00:12:56,955 --> 00:13:06,582
[SPEAKER_30]: But we have Steve Smerdy, who's our communications director, is going to probably put up the slideshow as he gets access.

167
00:13:07,403 --> 00:13:11,666
[SPEAKER_30]: We also have our CFO, who's a member of this committee, Bob Dickinson.

168
00:13:13,989 --> 00:13:31,662
[SPEAKER_30]: We have Jared Yargin, who is the city assessor, who helped us with these calculations, and Paul Riggi, who is our facilities maintenance director, was our facilities maintenance director, still staying on with the city to do several hours a week.

169
00:13:32,642 --> 00:13:38,404
[SPEAKER_30]: So I just want to thank them all for joining me tonight as we get through this presentation.

170
00:13:38,824 --> 00:13:40,025
[SPEAKER_30]: So Steve, if you could put it up.

171
00:13:40,065 --> 00:13:43,926
[SPEAKER_30]: I'm going to just make a few comments first, and then we'll work through it as a team.

172
00:13:43,946 --> 00:13:53,870
[SPEAKER_30]: I first want to start and just let everybody know that as a graduate of Medford High School, I'm well aware of the challenges of the existing high school building.

173
00:13:54,630 --> 00:14:12,440
[SPEAKER_30]: I'm also aware of the opportunity that our school programming provides and how this is an important step for Medford and our students, educators, staff to have an educationally appropriate modern facilities that supports the exceptional education that our school system is known for.

174
00:14:13,453 --> 00:14:24,483
[SPEAKER_30]: While there are other comprehensive high schools in the Commonwealth, Medford is unique in the path we took to get here, to provide a kid's access to a broader selection of offerings under one roof.

175
00:14:25,143 --> 00:14:31,168
[SPEAKER_30]: Our community asked us to merge the two high schools that operated separately side by side for over 50 years.

176
00:14:31,789 --> 00:14:35,312
[SPEAKER_30]: This year was the first year the school operated as a single comprehensive high school.

177
00:14:36,002 --> 00:14:43,866
[SPEAKER_30]: While this is a great first step, the current building does not support the collaboration and cross-pollination of ideas that we know are possible.

178
00:14:44,926 --> 00:14:50,168
[SPEAKER_30]: Medford currently has one of the most robust career technical education offerings in the state.

179
00:14:50,709 --> 00:14:56,731
[SPEAKER_30]: We have 723 students enrolled in CTE courses across 15 programs.

180
00:14:57,011 --> 00:14:58,512
[SPEAKER_30]: That's over half of our students.

181
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:04,675
[SPEAKER_30]: We also have 628 students enrolled in honors and AP courses, again, over half of our students.

182
00:15:05,918 --> 00:15:12,741
[SPEAKER_30]: We should be incredibly proud of this, of our teachers and staff and educational leadership that have made this school so exceptional.

183
00:15:13,342 --> 00:15:17,924
[SPEAKER_30]: Their vision for a brighter future for the children of Medford is inspiring and has my full support.

184
00:15:18,764 --> 00:15:24,027
[SPEAKER_30]: We are designing something incredibly special and we have one opportunity to get it right for the entire community.

185
00:15:25,145 --> 00:15:29,868
[SPEAKER_30]: We do have work to do, especially in the early fall to reduce the scope and cost.

186
00:15:30,368 --> 00:15:38,532
[SPEAKER_30]: But I'm confident this committee will do the hard work with me to make this a reality for our students, while also keeping in mind how this will affect everyone who lives in Medford.

187
00:15:38,552 --> 00:15:45,896
[SPEAKER_30]: I'm about to present a look at how our high school project, as it currently stands, costs out from different perspectives.

