00:44:38,521 --> 00:44:50,406
[SPEAKER_30]: We did these estimates just knowing that the current square footage is 640,000 square feet and what that impact would be as it relates to cleaning and maintenance.

431
00:44:50,426 --> 00:44:52,507
[SPEAKER_30]: So Paul, I'll let you take this one.

432
00:44:53,551 --> 00:44:56,012
[SPEAKER_20]: Sure, so good evening.

433
00:44:56,152 --> 00:45:02,615
[SPEAKER_20]: The 1 thing everyone needs to remember is that once we build a building, we need to take care of it.

434
00:45:03,875 --> 00:45:10,758
[SPEAKER_20]: Something that has been neglected over the years in Medford, and it's starting to turn around and.

435
00:45:11,618 --> 00:45:15,362
[SPEAKER_20]: This is what projected costs would be to the school system.

436
00:45:15,442 --> 00:45:17,364
[SPEAKER_20]: This is in today's dollars.

437
00:45:17,444 --> 00:45:22,770
[SPEAKER_20]: This is not projected out what it would be in five, six, seven years.

438
00:45:23,150 --> 00:45:29,817
[SPEAKER_20]: Cleaning could be a million dollars if a standard compensation ordinance is enacted.

439
00:45:31,118 --> 00:45:34,440
[SPEAKER_20]: Today's dollars would be 1.2 to 1.4 million.

440
00:45:35,421 --> 00:45:38,203
[SPEAKER_20]: HVAC maintenance, that's not for repairs.

441
00:45:38,963 --> 00:45:48,289
[SPEAKER_20]: That's for a company to maintain the system, a P&M contract, which is going to be needed with this new building.

442
00:45:49,310 --> 00:45:54,753
[SPEAKER_20]: The HVAC needs to be protected, needs to be taken care of annually.

443
00:45:55,234 --> 00:45:58,136
[SPEAKER_20]: A company needs to be brought online to do that.

444
00:45:58,936 --> 00:46:00,237
[SPEAKER_20]: Same thing with the elevators.

445
00:46:00,698 --> 00:46:02,379
[SPEAKER_20]: Currently, that does not happen.

446
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:04,821
[SPEAKER_20]: Just repairs take place.

447
00:46:05,842 --> 00:46:13,649
[SPEAKER_20]: A contract needs to be put in place for an elevator company to come in monthly and PM the elevators in the building.

448
00:46:14,009 --> 00:46:15,410
[SPEAKER_20]: Now, that's per elevator.

449
00:46:15,490 --> 00:46:17,532
[SPEAKER_20]: So, if you have 5 elevators, that's going to be $50,000.

450
00:46:17,592 --> 00:46:18,152
[SPEAKER_20]: And then utilities.

451
00:46:21,550 --> 00:46:23,452
[SPEAKER_20]: Now, this is a hard one to project.

452
00:46:23,732 --> 00:46:29,337
[SPEAKER_20]: Currently, the cost for the electricity for the current high school is about $690,000 a year.

453
00:46:29,357 --> 00:46:30,157
[SPEAKER_20]: But if you electrify,

454
00:46:35,968 --> 00:46:38,049
[SPEAKER_20]: that cost is going to go up.

455
00:46:38,689 --> 00:46:43,712
[SPEAKER_20]: I have a 40,000 square foot building totally electrified.

456
00:46:43,732 --> 00:46:57,399
[SPEAKER_20]: I'm paying $220,000 a year for electric because you have to remember when heating season comes, it's being heated by electric boilers if it's designed that way.

457
00:46:57,879 --> 00:47:02,902
[SPEAKER_20]: So a very careful choice in HVAC system needs to be made

458
00:47:03,662 --> 00:47:14,448
[SPEAKER_20]: made that it's not only green, it's not only electrified, but it also is going to provide cost savings and real savings and not just use electric.

459
00:47:16,070 --> 00:47:33,396
[SPEAKER_20]: I just need to caution everyone that I really don't want to see the city go the way of Lexington, who just approved their building and their superintendent was just faced with cutting 65 FTEs from the current upcoming budget.

460
00:47:34,316 --> 00:47:44,820
[SPEAKER_20]: One of the reasons is because they're so extended on their debt exclusion that they have no room to go out and ask the voters for more.

461
00:47:45,620 --> 00:47:48,502
[SPEAKER_20]: So we really need to be careful in Medford.

462
00:47:48,702 --> 00:48:00,792
[SPEAKER_20]: I agree, we need a new high school, but we need to make very careful choices, not only for the students, not only for the staff, but also for the taxpayers.

463
00:48:04,154 --> 00:48:05,095
[SPEAKER_30]: Thank you, Paul.

464
00:48:05,515 --> 00:48:07,436
[SPEAKER_30]: Last slide, I believe.

465
00:48:09,358 --> 00:48:09,498
[SPEAKER_30]: Yep.

466
00:48:09,778 --> 00:48:10,539
[SPEAKER_30]: Where do we go from here?

467
00:48:10,579 --> 00:48:14,182
[SPEAKER_30]: The city and Medford Public Schools will work together over the summer to develop a plan

468
00:48:15,281 --> 00:48:21,424
[SPEAKER_30]: to reduce costs by reducing spaces that are beyond the high school educational programming needs.

469
00:48:21,504 --> 00:48:35,170
[SPEAKER_30]: Beginning in September of 2026, that plan will be presented to the community for consideration and feedback before asking the school building committee to vote to finalize scope for this project to right size the building and in doing so to reduce costs.

470
00:48:35,871 --> 00:48:40,493
[SPEAKER_30]: And the city will continue to think creatively about project funding and ways to lessen the impact.

471
00:48:41,038 --> 00:48:45,359
[SPEAKER_30]: as well as we are looking into the Curtis Tufts School, doing an assessment on that building.

472
00:48:45,839 --> 00:48:51,181
[SPEAKER_30]: Hopefully will take place for Labor Day for the city of Edford.

473
00:48:53,221 --> 00:48:54,602
[SPEAKER_30]: I believe that's the last slide.

474
00:48:55,142 --> 00:49:05,265
[SPEAKER_30]: And I know I mentioned that we have our CFO, our assessor, somebody from our facilities maintenance team, and our commissioner of public works on the call if anybody has any questions.

